oslo_versionedobjects/fields.py.message:
The function's "obj" parameter is not an object of the class from the result of `obj_classes[value.object_field_name][0]`. I think you must be aware of this since you have called the field's "obj_from_primitive" class directly in the later commit, while "obj" is not an object of field class.

Taking the "InstanceNUMACell" example,

```
class InstanceNUMACell(...) {

fields = { ObjectField(ClassFiledA) }

}
```
when code comes here, L816, in a call of "InstanceNUMACell.obj_from_primitive", the parameter "obj" refers to an InstanceNUMACell object, and parameter "value" refers to class ClassFiledA.

Just as you did in the patch set 3, I agree that we could call the field class's "obj_from_primitive" directly.

